These instructions are to setup your development environment. 

= Packages needed =

<pre>
apt-get install python python-wxgtk2.8 python-imaging python-psyco python-pyopenssl python-gconf
</pre>

=== Packages needed only by the stable version ===

<pre>
apt-get install python-numeric python-numeric-ext 
</pre>

=== Packages needed only by the development version ===

<pre>
apt-get install python-numpy python-numpy-ext python-pygame python-avahi avahi-daemon
</pre>
        
= Getting the code =

You will then need to install "cogito" (<tt>apt-get install cogito</tt>) and run the following

== For stable version ==
<pre>
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/scratchpad.git
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/libtpproto-py.git
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/libtpclient-py.git
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/tpclient-pywx.git

# Setup various links
cd scratchpad
./setup.sh
cd ..

# Check all the requirements are satisified
cd tpclient-pywx
pythonw requirements.py

# Now run the client!
pythonw tpclient-pywx
</pre>

== For development version ==
<pre>
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/scratchpad.git
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/libtpproto-py.git
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/libtpclient-py.git#development libtpclient-py-dev
cg-clone git://git.thousandparsec.net/git/tpclient-pywx.git#development tpclient-pywx-dev

# Setup various links
cd scratchpad
./setup.sh
cd ..

# Check all the requirements are satisified
cd tpclient-pywx
pythonw requirements.py

# Now run the client!
pythonw tpclient-pywx
</pre>